## Strategic Integration of Performance Management, Training, and Compensation

### Alignment with Organizational Goals

Strategic human resource management establishes competency standards for each job role, which PMS measures and rewards. This alignment ensures that day-to-day operations contribute to the companyâ€™s vision and objectives ([AzCentral](https://yourbusiness.azcentral.com/between-performance-management-system-strategic-human-resource-management-28305.html)).

### Congruency and Competency Models

Implementing a robust PMS requires a defined strategy that communicates organizational goals to all employees. Competency models serve as frameworks for evaluating performance and guiding training and compensation decisions ([Business Training Works](https://www.businesstrainingworks.com/onsite-courses/performance-management-systems-training-course/)).

### Separation of Performance Measurement and Development

To optimize both compensation and development, organizations should separate performance measurement (used for compensation decisions) from developmental feedback (focused on growth). This distinction allows for more frequent development conversations, enhancing intrinsic motivation and reducing the negative impact of extrinsic motivators like compensation discussions during performance reviews ([Culture Amp](https://www.cultureamp.com/blog/performance-management-and-development)).

